Sri Lankan Food Department officialssaid the U.S. Department of Agriculture rejected a U.S. Firm'soffer of 80 U.S. Dlrs per tonne CAF to supply 52,500 tonnes ofsoft wheat to Colombo from the Pacific Northwest.    They said Sri Lanka's Food Department subsequently made acounter-offer to five U.S. Firms to buy wheat at 85 U.S. DlrsCAF for April 8-16 delivery.    The company which obtains USDA approval for the proposedprice must inform the Department before 1330 gmt, they said. REUTER&#3;